genresAdvancedInfo.name: italian classical guitar
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Italian classical guitar music is a genre that showcases the beauty and versatility of the guitar. It draws on the rich tradition of classical music in Italy, and features intricate fingerpicking, melodic runs, and complex harmonies. Italian classical guitarists often perform pieces by composers such as Vivaldi and Paganini, as well as original compositions that showcase their virtuosity and musicality. Whether performing in a concert hall or on the streets of Rome, Italian classical guitar music is sure to captivate
